ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.128                Enzyme
NAME        beta-cubebene synthase;
            cop4;
            Mg25
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate diphosphate-lyase (cyclizing, beta-cubebene-forming)
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate = beta-cubebene + diphosphate [RN:R10007]
ALL_REAC    R10007
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448]
PRODUCT     beta-cubebene [CPD:C09648];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     Isolated from the fungus Coprinus cinereus. The enzyme also forms (+)-delta-cadinene, beta-copaene, (+)-sativene and traces of several other sequiterpenoids [2-4]. It is found in many higher plants such as Magnolia grandiflora (Southern Magnolia) together with germacrene A [1]. See EC 4.2.3.13, (+)-delta-cadinene synthase, EC 4.2.3.127, beta-copaene synthase, EC 4.2.3.129, (+)-sativene synthase, and EC 4.2.3.23, germacrene A synthase.
HISTORY     EC 4.2.3.128 created 2012
